  "title": "deacons",
  "comment": "Those who ``serve'' in the Christian community, assisting the elders or overseers (bishops). The Greek word which the NIV translates four times as ``deacon'' occurs a further 25 times in the NT, where it is translated as ``servant''. It seems that all Christians have a general servant role, whereas some (deacons) are called to a specific office of service within the church.",
